<dl id="n53124p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53124p">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53124p"> 124(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> looking for the / builder, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53124p"><li>FW 62.08 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n53124p">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n53124p">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53124p">MS BL 47476b-178</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:377 <a name="cd10" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n53124p">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Il s&apos;&eacute;cria: <p>&laquo;J&apos;ai eu d&apos;innombrables naissances. <mark>Je cherchais</mark>, toujours vainement, <mark>le constructeur</mark> de la maison. Ah, qu&apos;il est douloureux de rena&icirc;tre sans cesse! O constructeur de la maison, voici que tu es d&eacute;couvert. Tu ne construis plus de maison. Les liens sont bris&eacute;s qui rattachaiant tes c&ocirc;tes. La vieille cl&ocirc;ture est rompue; l&apos;antique montagne s&apos;effondre; l&apos;esprit touche le nirv&acirc;na; la naissance n&apos;est plus, car le d&eacute;sir n&apos;est plus.&raquo;</p> <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 90f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Siddhartha realised that he had for many years looked for the builder of the house of existence and now at last he had found him. </mm> </dd></dl>
